article.description: Charles Odum scored 21 points and Portland State rallied for a 93-89 victory over Cal State-Fullerton on Sunday.
article.headline: Cal State Fullerton blows 11-point lead in loss
article.linkText: Cal State Fullerton blows 11-point lead in loss
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Charles Odum scored 21 points and Portland State rallied for a 93-89 victory over Cal State-Fullerton on Sunday. Chris Harriel added 20 points, including 18 in the second half, and Melvin Jones chipped in 18 points as the Vikings (6-2) won their sixth straight home game. Orane Chin led the Titans (3-7) with 32 points and Jer'Vaughn Johnson had 19. Portland State rallied from an 11-point deficit in the final 13:40 thanks to 16 points from Harriel down the stretch. Harriel scored 13 straight at one point to cut the Fullerton lead to 79-77 with 3:10 to play. The Vikings took their first lead of the second half, 84-83, with 1 minute remaining when Chehales Tapscott hit two free throws. After Chin fouled out, Odum converted a three-point play to put the Vikings up 87-83 and then hit six straight free throws to secure the victory.
